                <li>Nesting lists and creating sub-lists.</li>
                <li>Customizing list styles with CSS.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">HTML Semantic Elements:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Understanding semantic HTML and its importance.</li>
                <li>Using semantic elements like: &lt;nav&gt;, &lt;section&gt;, &lt;aside&gt;, &lt;main&gt;, 
                    &lt;footer&gt;, &lt;article&gt;,&lt;header&gt;</li>
                <li>Improving accessibility and search engine optimization (SEO).</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">HTML5 Features:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>New HTML5 elements like &lt;video&gt;, &lt;audio&gt;, &lt;canvas&gt;, &lt;svg&gt; etc.</li>
                <li>Geolocation API.</li>
                <li>Local storage and session storage.</li>
                <li>Web Workers and Web Sockets.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">Responsive Web Design with <br>HTML and CSS:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Building responsive layouts using HTML and CSS.</a></li>
                <li>Media queries and breakpoints.</li>
                <li>Responsive images and videos.</li>
                <li>Mobile-first approach and fluid grids.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">Embedding External Content:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Embedding videos from YouTube or Vimeo.</li>
                <li>Including Google Maps.</li>
                <li>Integrating social media widgets.</li>
                <li>Adding custom code snippets (e.g., JavaScript libraries).</li>
            </ol>
