                <h4 style="margin-left: 1vw;">HTML entities are&nbsp;written with (&entityname;) format. Examples:</h4>
                <p>
                    &#9622; Please do not use the &lt;code&gt; element for formatting text in HTML.<br>
                    &#8627; Sites with &copy; have copyrights<br>
                    &#8259; The &gt; symbol is often used in mathematics to indicate greater than.<br>
                    &#8270; He said, 'I love programming,' and then added, &quot;It's my passion!&quot;<br>
                    &#8227; The &apos; character is frequently used to represent feet or minutes in some contexts.<br>
                    &#8226; This product is protected by the &reg; trademark. Unauthorized reproduction is prohibited.<br>
                    &#8208; The price of the item is €100. Please make your payment in Euros.<br>
                    &#10625; This logo is marked with the &trade; symbol, indicating it's a registered trademark.<br>
                    &#10634; Use &nbsp; to add extra spacing between words in HTML when necessary.<br>
                    &#10695; The sentence—containing an em dash—provides additional information.<br>
                    &#10731; The event will take place from June 10&ndash;12, so mark your calendars!<br>
